# CSS is used to control the appearance of an HTML element
h1 {
   color: red;
}

#CSS Rules
A CSS rule starts with a selector. A selector specifies which HTML elements to style. Here the h1 CSS selector selects all h1 HTML elements on the page.
e the braces { }, a property and its value define what aspect of the h1 elements to style. Setting the color property to red changes the color of the h1 element to red.

#Class Attribute en html
<div class="header">
Class selector en CSS
.heard {
  color: blue;
}
ou en combinant : 
.header p {
  color: blue
}

